%h1 My panel
%p Use the options below to manage your data

.row.row-cols-1.row-cols-md-2.g-4
  
  .col.d-flex.align-items-stretch
    .card.w-100
      .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
        %h5.card-title
          Categories
        %p.card-text
          Each expense belongs to a category and a subcategory.
          %a{"data-bs-toggle" => "tooltip", "data-bs-placement" => "top", "data-bs-title" => "Example: expenses for a car can belong to the category \"transportation\" and one of the following subcategories: \"fuel\", \"maintenance\" or \"repair\". "}
            %svg.bi.pe-none.me-2{ :width => "16", :height => "16", "aria-hidden" => "true" }
              %use{ "xlink:href" => "#info" }
        = link_to "Manage categories", categories_path, {class: "btn btn-fakturo align-self-stretch mt-auto"}

  .col.d-flex.align-items-stretch
    .card.w-100
      .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
        %h5.card-title 
          Sources
        %p.card-text
          Sources of expenses, like checking accounts and credit cards.
          %a{"data-bs-toggle" => "tooltip", "data-bs-placement" => "top", "data-bs-title" => "They can be registered as \"Bank X\" and \"Credit card Y\" and will be linked to the expenses. Sources emit statements."}
            %svg.bi.pe-none.me-2{ :width => "16", :height => "16", "aria-hidden" => "true" }
              %use{ "xlink:href" => "#info" }
        = link_to "Manage sources", sources_path, {class: "btn btn-fakturo align-self-stretch mt-auto"}
  
  .col.d-flex.align-items-stretch
    .card.w-100
      .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
        %h5.card-title 
          Statements
        %p.card-text
          Statements are collections of expenses.
          %a{"data-bs-toggle" => "tooltip", "data-bs-placement" => "top", "data-bs-title" => "They belong to an institution (source) and are produced in a regular interval, usually monthly. Think of \"Statement for the month of april from Bank X\"."}
            %svg.bi.pe-none.me-2{ :width => "16", :height => "16", "aria-hidden" => "true" }
              %use{ "xlink:href" => "#info" }
        .alert.alert-info
          When you upload a statement, the expenses it contains will be automatically extracted and registered in the system.
        = link_to "Manage statements", statements_path, {class: "btn btn-fakturo align-self-stretch mt-auto"}
        

  .col.d-flex.align-items-stretch
    .card
      .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
        %h5.card-title Expenses
        %p.card-text
          Each line in a checking account statement or credit card statement is an expense. 
          %br
          %br
          Here you can manage extracted expenses from uploaded statements or create them manually.
        = link_to "Manage expenses", expenses_path, {class: "btn btn-fakturo align-self-stretch mt-auto"}
